Interface DoorAccessCommManager.OnBoardCommReceiveListener

  • Enclosing class:
    DoorAccessCommManager

    public static interface DoorAccessCommManager.OnBoardCommReceiveListener
    Callback will be triggered while android board receiving message from MCU board.

    • Method Detail

      • onBoardHeartbeat

        void onBoardHeartbeat(byte[] cardCount,
                      byte[] crc,
                      byte[] curTime,
                      byte[] bluetoothMac,
                      byte[] bluetoothName)
        The heartbeat callback including the following data
        Parameters:
        cardCount - byte[2] Total number of card numbers owned by this board
        crc - byte[4] CRC32 for all data
        curTime - byte[5] current swipe board time
        bluetoothMac - byte[6] bluetooth MAC Address
        bluetoothName - byte[8] Bluetooth name

      • onBoardPostAccessRecord

        void onBoardPostAccessRecord(byte[] cardId,
                             byte[] startDateTime,
                             byte[] endDateTime,
                             byte[] curDateTime,
                             byte[] phoneNum,
                             byte accessMode)
        Callback while user swiping IC or ID card on MCU board. It will return card id as follows.
        Parameters:
        cardId - byte[8] card id
        startDateTime - byte[5] start time
        endDateTime - byte[5] end time
        curDateTime - byte[5] current time
        phoneNum - byte[5] phone number
        accessMode - byte unlock mode

      • onBoardLockTongueState

        void onBoardLockTongueState(byte state,
                            byte[] curDateTime)
        Callback of MCU reports lock tongue status
        Parameters:
        state - byte lock tongue status, 0 ---lock open，1--- lock closed
        curDateTime - byte[5] current date time
